  <facilityDescription><![CDATA[<p><span style="text-decoration: underline;"><strong>Restaurants &amp; Bars</strong></span></p>
<p><strong>Timeo Restaurant</strong> is one of the most scenic restaurants in Taormina. A large terrace stretches infront of the hotel with superb views across the town and Mount Etna. Mouth-watering cuisine is based on typical Sicilian dishes that are complemented by a menu of regional wines. Open for lunch and dinner.</p>
<p><strong>The Literary Terrace and Bar</strong> offers classic cocktails and fine wines that can be enjoyed with incredible views towards Mount Etna.</p>
<p><strong>Pool Restaurant and Bar</strong> serves brick-oven pizzas, grilled fish and a fresh salad bar under the shade of vine-covered pergolas.</p>
<p><span style="text-decoration: underline;"><strong>Pool &amp; Beach</strong></span></p>
<p>A heated pool is surrounded by established gardens and comfortable loungers with views of Mount Etna. A pool bar is in hand for light lunches and refreshments (during summer)</p>
<p>Guests are able to take a complimentary shuttle to the private beach of Belmond Villa Sant’Andrea where you’ll find sun loungers, beach cabanas (payable locally) and a restaurant.</p>
<p><span style="text-decoration: underline;"><strong>Spa</strong></span></p>
<p>The spa at Belmond Grand Hotel Timeo offers treatments using organic products with healing local herbs and Neroli oil. <br />Guests are also able to use the hotel’s fitness centre.</p>
<p><span style="text-decoration: underline;"><strong>General Facilities</strong></span></p>
<ul>
<li>Shuttle service to Belmond Villa Sant’Andrea</li>
<li>Free wifi</li>
</ul>]]></facilityDescription>
